CatDescriptText: Mrs. Arnie Sowell, state employee, 1H Lillian Drive, McKees Rocks, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 13, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the hospital service rendered under Blue Cross plan is worth its present cost to the subscriber? Do you think the rates should be raised?  Why?"  answer reads: "Actually, I think that I would receive good service for rates which I am paying for Blue Cross.  But as for the increase in rates, I am against that because I feel that they are already high enough."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. Arnie Sowell wearing light colored button down blouse with short sleeves and stand up collar, standing outside of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
